Oh dear! Badly done. In no way do I defend the offensive remarks made. (So please no trolling for what I’m about to write.)
What that woman said was an unfortunate use of words. By that, I mean a Brit unless they have lived years in the USA will not have a clue what that phrase actually means in USA culture. Just like when Americans say British slang phrases, ie bloody, shag, buggar & others will not know how offensive these words mean to Brits.
As an American, married to a posh Brit and lived in the UK more years than I like to admit, is that Americans do not fully, deeply understand British culture and likewise.
Americans really seem to believe that the British are anti-Meghan due to race. Hand on heart, that really is not the issue. Or if it is, it makes up only a very small part of the population. Do you not remember when Meghan was introduced first as Prince Harry’s girlfriend, and then fiancé, the public and press welcome was overwhelmingly positive?!?The country was euphoric with delight that this vibrant woman was Harry’s lover. At first, many people did not even know Meghan was bi-racial. Nor did it matter until others started to say it mattered. If you do your research, you’ll find that the UK has the highest number of mixed-raced married couples in the world. The race issue is simply spin IMO.
What the British public and press began to take exception to was Meghan’s apparent unwillingness to follow even the simplest of British Royal protocols. Nor did she appear to care much for Brit culture and life. She was constantly advised to take her time, lie low and learn about her newly adopted country. Even First Lady Michelle Obama advise much the same.
However, this appears to not be Meghan’s preferred style of operation. As a result, faux pas after faux pas began happening and then reported upon. That combined with her mysterious rejection of her family, followed with her family’s interview efforts only added fuel to that fire.

As the past year and half progressed, Meghan’s apparent upstaging of other Royal Family events has been viewed as not just disrespect to HMTQ, but also either a direct refusal to listen to the Palaces’ directions regarding PR event schedules to eventually regarded as intentional sabotage.
For those that are not British and have not grown up with the Royal Family always being a part of the background of your life, much of the culture simply isn’t known nor understood. For example, it was not HM The Queen who made it impossible for Meghan and Prince Harry to use “Royal” as part of their brand name. It’s actually a British law going way, way back which determines who and how a “Royal” warrant (brand allegiance) can be used. The Queen possibly may have reminded the couple of this fact, but it was actually Parliament some 100+ years ago which made this law. Despite this distinction, American media was out in full force blaming The Queen and the Royal Family. The fact is, Prince Harry should have known this already.
Finally, as an American living here in Britain for years, Americans do not initially understand that The British Royal Family is very operated like a non-for-profit company. By that, instead of making a profit, they are very much like a combo of being chief British diplomats and chief patrons of British charities. Their various PR functions and events are NOT to enhance their own personal celebrity, but that of the charity they represent and at times as diplomats the United Kingdom. So when one family member ignores the Royal schedule of events and trots out on their own and steals the limelight, it’s very much frowned upon. Why is this so important an issue? Because, some poor charity or NGO which has counted on royal publicity to help spread their good cause and help with donations is totally upstaged by a more press popular Royal. Thus, making all the efforts of the palaces and the organisation wasted. The charities have the most to lose in such situations.
THIS is why PH and Meghan have fallen from favour in the UK and parts of The Commonwealth. It’s not so much because she’s American or bi-racial.

Falun Dafa, also known as Falun Gong, is an ancient spiritual and meditation practice based on the principles of Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance. Not only have practitioners benefited from the practice, but many people who don’t practice Falun Dafa have also seen their health improve and danger averted.

Below are two such stories.

My Husband’s Coronavirus Symptoms Disappeared
My husband, in his 80s, usually gets up very early every day. He lives in a different house and usually comes over to my house every morning. On February 3, 2020, however, I still hadn't seen him as of 10 a.m. Just as I thought about going over to check on him, he showed up at my house. He said he had been vomiting the whole morning and his entire body ached. He also felt tightness in his chest and had a fever of 38.6°C.

Upon learning his situation, our family became very worried and sent him to the local clinic, which happened to be closed on that day.

What should we do? With no hospital nearby, I asked him to recite “Falun Dafa is good; Truthfulness, Compassion, Forbearance is good.” As a practitioner of Falun Dafa, I know that many people have received blessings after reciting the phrases.

I gave him a few fever pills and asked him to stay in bed. I also read Zhuan Falun, the main teachings of Falun Dafa, to him. After a while, he fell asleep.

After he woke up, his condition improved and his body temperature dropped to 37.5°C. On the next day, his temperature returned to normal, but he still felt weak. By the third day, he regained most of his strength and had appetite again. All of our family are grateful to Master for saving his life!

“I Truly Believe in It This Time”
A Falun Dafa practitioner in Henan Province said she has a neighbor in her 80s and she often asked her to recite “Falun Dafa is good.”

One day, the elderly woman’s husband suddenly lost consciousness and fell to the ground. His face was pale. With no one else nearby to help her, the elderly woman recited “Falun Dafa is good. Master Li, please save my husband.”

Just as she was repeating the phrases, her husband woke up and his face was no longer pale. After her children came back, they sent him to the hospital for a thorough checkup. The doctor said he was doing fine and discharged him a few days later.

The elderly woman said she knew another woman in her 50s, who collapsed just like her husband, and later died.

Her husband, who didn’t believe in Falun Dafa before, now changed his mind. “I truly believe in it this time. Thank you, Master Li!”
